This paper deals with the synchronization of nonlinear systems, which is a topic that is relevant to several subfields of computer science. The use of contraction theory suggests that the paper may be related to control theory and systems engineering, which are often categorized under cs.SY. The mention of neuronal networks suggests that the paper may also be related to computational neuroscience (cs.NE). The use of network theory and the exploration of the influence of network structure suggests that the paper may be related to dynamical systems (cs.DS) and mathematical analysis (cs.MA). Finally, the mention of control of complex networked systems suggests that the paper may be related to social and information networks (cs.SI).
